paragraphs.text:
%md
# Monte-Carlo Simulation of an Euler-Scheme discretization of a Black-Scholes Model

Simple demonstration of a Monte-Carlo simulation of Black Scholes model. We perform a Monte-Carlo simulation of an Euler discretization of the classical Black-Scholes model
\\[ \mathrm{d}S(t) = r S(t) \mathrm{d}t + \sigma S(t) \mathrm{d}W(t) ,\, S(0) = S_{0} \\]
where \\( r \\) denotes the risk free rate, \\( \sigma \\) denotes the volatility, \\( S_{0} \\) the inital value (spot).

msg.data:
Monte-Carlo Simulation of an Euler-Scheme discretization of a Black-Scholes Model

Simple demonstration of a Monte-Carlo simulation of Black Scholes model. We perform a Monte-Carlo simulation of an Euler discretization of the classical Black-Scholes model
\[ \mathrm{d}S(t) = r S(t) \mathrm{d}t + \sigma S(t) \mathrm{d}W(t) ,\, S(0) = S_{0} \]
where \( r \) denotes the risk free rate, \( \sigma \) denotes the volatility, \( S_{0} \) the inital value (spot).
